Coefficient plots from mixed effects models of democracy. The sample includes 169 countries from as early as 1920 to 2022. The model includes 4 years of lags of democracy, which explain most of the variance but were omitted from the chart. The reference category for form of government is presidential systems. The options on the right update the plot based on the interactions with the form of government. The estimates and confidence intervals for the intercept, Parties, and Ethnic diversity are adjusted based on the estimates and standard errors from the interaction terms.
